reorganize

public void reorganize(TemporalObject<E> currentStatus,
                       int ID)
                throws IllegalStateException
Description copied from class: ListSA
In contrast to the method ListSA.expire(Object, int), this method removes all expired elements from a ListSA without returning them. The reorganization follows the internal linkage provided by a ListSA. In the lazy reorganization mode, as long as removePredicates[ID].invoke(list.get(0), currentStatus) holds impl.remove(list.remove(0)) is called. In the save memory reorganization mode, the whole list is checked for exprired elements

Specified by:
reorganize in interface SweepArea<TemporalObject<E>>
Overrides:
reorganize in class ListSA<TemporalObject<E>>
Parameters:
currentStatus - The object containing the necessary information to perform the reorganization step.
ID - An ID determining from which input this reorganization step is triggered.
Throws:
IllegalStateException - Throws an IllegalStateException if this method is called at an invalid state.
